BEY
v.
UNITED STATES 2018-1648 Supreme Court of Ohio. January 15, 2019

CASE ANNOUNCEMENTS

MOTION AND PROCEDURAL RULINGS

Miscellaneous case. On motions for admission pro hac vice of Philip Back and Francis C. Fredericks and amended motion for admission pro hac vice of Adrian Kowalski. Motions granted contingent on the admitted attorneys' renewing their certificates of registration for 2019 as required by S.Ct.Prac.R. 2.02(D)(2). Pursuant to Gov.Bar R. XII(4), counsel shall file a notice of permission with the Supreme Court's Office of Attorney Services within 30 days.
